<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODGERS-MARINERS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GRUDZIELANEK LIFTS DODGERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ In a dismal season when the Dodgers respond to
nothing for the long-term and the fans have nothing to embrace,
something finally happened to excite folks.
</P>
<P>
   Mark Grudzielanek drove in four runs _ three with a
second-inning homer _ and made a stellar defensive play at
shortstop as the Dodgers beat the Mariners 5-0 Friday in an
interleague contest at Dodger Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   It came after Dodgers general manager Kevin Malone addressed the
team for nearly 45 minutes in a closed-door meeting to deliver a
candid message: The season isn't over, the Dodgers aren't out of
it, and if you don't think you can win or you don't want to win,
you don't belong here.
</P>
<P>
   It was the Dodgers' third meeting in less than a week, which
equals the number of wins they've had during that span.
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers' first shutout win since May 3, buoyed by Ismael
Valdes' seven strong innings, also represents their second straight
win. That's something they hadn't done since June 25-26. They
haven't won three straight since a five-game streak April 27 to May
1.
</P>
<P>
   Grudzielanek, who spent 28 days on the disabled list, was a big
part of both wins. When he returned earlier this week in Colorado,
the difference in Grudzielanek's approach was noticeable.
</P>
<P>
   After missing five weeks with a broken right hand, the remnants
of punching a wall after hitting into a double play in Pittsburgh,
Grudzielanek has seven hits in 14 at-bats.
</P>
<P>
   ``I tried to tell myself, `You have to have a plan when you come
back,' '' Grudzielanek said. ``Rick (Down, the Dodgers' hitting
coach) and I would go back to the batting cages, and I couldn't use
my right hand, so I had one of those small bats and I swung with
one hand. It helps you stay back, keep your bat back.''
</P>
<P>
   It worked in Colorado, where Grudzielanek went 5 for 10 after
being activated for Tuesday's game. A first-inning, three-run
double keyed Thursday's win against the Rockies. Friday, it was his
bat again that gave Valdes (7-7) an early lead an inning after the
Dodgers loaded the bases with none out but saw Todd Hundley, Raul
Mondesi and Devon White each struck out by Freddy Garcia.
</P>
<P>
   Instead, they came back with a pair of base runners for
Grudzielanek, who batted leadoff for the second time this season.
</P>
<P>
   Grudzielanek, who's last homer came April 25 and spanned 121
at-bats, drove Garcia's pitch over the left-center field fence to
give the Dodgers a 3-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
   ``I looked at some old tapes and saw that I was hitting the ball
the other way,'' Grudzielanek said. ``They can put two fielders
over there and I'm still going to try that. That's what I did when
I had my (all-star) year (1996). If you do that, you'll be able to
turn on some pitches.''
</P>
<P>
   Grudzielanek is expected to hit, and during the first stint of
his career on the disabled list, the Dodgers sorely missed his bat.
But defense was the problem, especially since he made 92 errors the
last three seasons.
</P>
<P>
   Although he spent most of the offseason working with Bucky Dent
on his defense, Grudzielanek has been OK at shortstop but rarely
made the sensational play. He did that in the fourth to save a run
for Valdes.
</P>
<P>
   With Dan Wilson on second and two outs, Brian Hunter hit a ball
into shallow left field. Grudzielanek ranged back, stretched his
glove back and made a back-hand catch before falling to the turf.
</P>
<P>
   In the bottom of the fifth the Dodgers made it 4-0 on Craig
Counsell's RBI single to left, which scored Mondesi and
Grudzielanek added an RBI single in the seventh.
</P>
<P>
   Valdes allowed seven hits, struck out four and hit two batters
in seven innings. Garcia (9-5) struck out 10, but he threw 123
pitches in five innings and allowed four runs on six hits. He also
walked four and hit two batters.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
