<HEADLINE>
EJECTION, NOT INJURY, KEEPS MILLER OFF SIDELINE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   However serious Cheryl Miller was about not coaching Friday
night as announced in the pregame notes, there she was, limping to
the bench on crutches to the cheers of 12,236.
</P>
<P>
   The 35-year-old, who had surgery Wednesday to repair a ruptured
Achilles' tendon suffered a day earlier during practice, held
little back. Wearing jeans to cover her cast, she hopped around
arguing with her usual verve at the officials.
</P>
<P>
   It was her objection to an offensive foul against Michele Timms
that rated a technical foul from Dennis DeMayo with 14:20
remaining. Lamont Simpson whistled the second T at 5:16, not long
after a three-pointer by Houston's Cynthia Cooper that instead
could have gone as a charge against Kristi Harrower.
</P>
<P>
   Miller also was ejected during an 80-76 loss at Orlando on June
21 and was ejected from one game each in 1997 and '98. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
