<HEADLINE>
SLIPPERY SLOPE ON THE PLAYING FIELD 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
 (NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact Olivia Vasquez in Los
Angeles (Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089)  
 (bl)  
 By GINA KOLATA   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   It happened again this year. Another drug scandal in sports.
This time, it involved more than a dozen cyclists in Swiss and
Italian races failing blood tests, including Marco Pantani of
Italy, last year's winner of the Tour de France.
</P>
<P>
   But some critics are pointing to what they see as a disconnect
between excessive worry over performance-enhancing drugs and
uncritical applause for the other ways of boosting an athlete's
