<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Get a sneak peek of `Eyes Wide Shut'
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ The late Stanley Kubrick didn't want you
to know anything about Eyes Wide Shut until the movie opens Friday.
But if you can't wait for some tidbits, consider seeking out these
sources:
</P>
<P>
   _ The novel: The movie is based on Austrian author Arthur
Schnitzler's erotic, mysterious ``Dream Story.'' Although copies
have been hard to find, at least one was in a south county Borders
recently.
</P>
<P>
   _ The memoir: ``Eyes Wide Open,'' a remembrance by Frederic
Raphael of working with Kubrick on the screenplay, was just
published and is full of juicy and controversial tidbits, from
Kubrick's views on Hitler to his insular working methods to
Raphael's splendid insights into Kubrick's mind-set.
</P>
<P>
   _ The magazines: Cruise and Kidman are on the covers of
magazines everywhere, but they're not saying much. Unless you're
intrigued that the long shoot gave Cruise an ulcer or that 65
seconds of nudity will be digitally covered up in the American
version to ensure an R-rating. Time magazine ran an early, positive
review last week and a chart that confirmed or squelched some of
the rumors (does Cruise kiss a dead woman or not?) And critic
Alexander Walker ran a review (also positive) that's available on
the Internet at www.thisislondon.co.uk
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
