that we are proceeding with all of the empirical data that one
should have. And it doesn't exist at this point.''
</P>
<P>
   EXPERTS REACT TO BOOMING DRUG
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Don Catlin runs the Olympic drug testing laboratory at UCLA.
At work each morning, he checks his e-mail and finds
by-now-familiar notes from colleagues around the world.
</P>
<P>
   ``They say things like, `What in the world is going on in
America?''' Catlin said. ``They can't understand how something like
