</P>
<P>
   But Girardi and others said that enforcement of any kind _
either through persuasion or policy _ would most likely be futile.
</P>
<P>
   ``Guys are going to do whatever they have to do to keep up with
the times,'' said Damion Easley of the Detroit Tigers. ``It doesn't
matter what the union or anybody else says. They'll do whatever
they have to do and worry about the consequences later.''
</P>
<P>
   A WORK IN PROGRESS
</P>
<P>
   When McGwire admitted last year that he had been taking, and
would continue to take, androstenedione, baseball officials and the
leaders of the players' union came to an agreement. Noting the
legality of andro, they pledged to conduct their own study to
evaluate the product's effects and risks. Two Harvard researchers
undertook the task.
</P>
<P>
   Now, nearly a year later, the researchers remain at work. In an
interview, one of the researchers, Dr. Benjamin Leder, conceded
that he ``agreed with about everything that was written'' in the
recent Iowa State study that asserted andro use might increase the
