suggestion of the study's author that the federal government
``carefully consider intervening and removing androstenedione and
its derivatives from the market.''
</P>
<P>
   Asked what he would recommend to a weekend athlete interested in
experimenting with andro, Leder said: ``I'd tell them little is
known about andro and its possible effects, both beneficial or
toxic side effects. Taking anything when not much is known about it
is risky.''
</P>
<P>
   Selig and Orza emphasized that they were determined to wait
until the study was done before coming to a conclusion.
</P>
<P>
   ``If the scientists conclude it's something risky, we'll tell
the players it's risky,'' Orza said. ``We're not going to be shoved
into this decision.''
</P>
<P>
   One major-league executive, who spoke on condition of anonymity,
said that baseball is cognizant of ``protecting'' McGwire.
</P>
<P>
   Both Selig and Orza ridicule such claims, calling them
``unfair'' and ``nonsense.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
