<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBO-GARCIAPARRA _ Boston's Nomar Garciaparra, a former Georgia
Tech Yellow Jacket and arguably the best shortstop in baseball,
discusses his accomplishments to date and what it will feel like to
start at shortstop in Boston. (Rosen, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
18-20. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   BBO-HOMERUNS _ We said last year that the HR chase that
mesmerized the nation could never happen again. But guess what?
With baseball at midseason, Jose Canseco, Sammy Sosa, Ken Griffey
Jr. and Mark McGwire are making record-setting HR races look more
and more like an annual affair. (Stinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-JACKIE-ROBINSON _ CAIRO, Ga. _ Jackie Robinson was a toddler
when his mother left Georgia on a train bound for California in
1920 and he returned to Cairo only once _ on Jackie Robinson Day in
1949. But the man who broke the color line in baseball with the
Brooklyn Dodgers is not forgotten in the place of his birth. A
highway through the south Georgia town is named for Robinson, as is
the high school baseball field. And some day Dr. Linda Walden _ a
distant cousin of Robinson _ and others hope a new recreation and
community center in Cairo will be built to honor the baseball
great's legacy. (Curtright, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   GOLF
</P>
<P>
   GLF-BROPEN-COURSE _ CARNOUSTIE, Scotland _ The Carnoustie course
in Scotland, which last played host to a British Open 24 years ago,
long has been regarded as one of the toughest in Europe. The
victims of that Open tell us why. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   GLF-BROPEN-NOTES _ CARNOUSTIE, Scotland _ British Open notebook.
(Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-KUCHAR _ CARNOUSTIE, Scotland _ One year ago, Georgia Tech
golfer Matt Kuchar had the golfing world in his hands. He had wowed
the sport with strong finishes at the Masters and U.S. Open and
headed toward the British Open with a major decision at hand.
Should he go pro and take the endorsement riches or return to Ga.
Tech? He chose to return to school. Now, on the eve of the 1999
British Open, Kuchar's game is in shambles. And he's thinking about
what might have been. (Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
MOVED
</P>
<P>
   GLF-BROPEN-GUIDE _ CARNOUSTIE, Scotland _ A reader's guide to
picking the British Open office pool. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25. MOVED
</P>
