<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   COKE-EUROPE _ BRUSSELS _ The health scare that has gripped
Europe this year goes far beyond the recent Coca-Cola crisis here.
After all, Belgium was an emotional/political/social tinderbox
waiting for something like the naive Coke to come along. A series
of scares from Mad Cow disease to E-coli to Genetically Modified
food to dioxin have people hyper-sensitive about food in Europe.
Added to this: a growing lack of faith in their governments'
ability to protect them _ as evidenced by the popular rejection of
Belgium's sitting government over the dioxin scare. All of these
forces came to bear when the first cases of Coke Sickness came
forward _ primarily involving adolescent girls. And here was a new
health minister in Belgium, who assumed his role when the last
health minister was forced out over the dioxin scare. Adding insult
to injury was Coke being, well, Coke, Arrogant and American and
MBA, it tried dealing with the situation from an American
perspective and allowed it to mushroom out of control. (Roughton,
Cox News Service). 35. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: MOVED Wednesday in (1) International and (f) Financial
categories.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   EUROPE-BOX _ BRUSSELS _ A list of the incidents that have led to
the ``health scare culture'' in Europe this year. (Roughton, Cox
News Service). 10. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: MOVED Wednesday in (1) International and (f) Financial
categories.
</P>
<P>
   CARE _ CARE staff members joke it's the Australian word for
chaos and CARE workers, it seems, are people who enjoy going about
doing good, especially if it involves a lot of going about. But
behind the flurry, there is a method and a commendable motive.
(Graham, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   MANAGED-CARE _ WASHINGTON _ The Senate returns this week to
debate and vote on one of the most politically charged battles on
its agenda _ whether to approve a ``patient's bill of rights'' that
would tighten regulation of the managed care industry. (Lipman, Cox
News Service). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   CHANGING-SOUTH _ (Reskedded to July 25)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   HEMINGWAY _ It may be Papa's 100th birthday, but the party in
one of his favorite haunts is having trouble getting off the
ground. Key West's annual Hemingway Festival has struggled to
survive since a tiff two years ago with the Hemingway family nearly
caused the event's cancellation. Organizers say this year's event
(July 16-21) will come off, despite a lack of corporate and
business support. Without more support, though, they aren't sure
the event will survive in years to come. (MWilliams, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
