<P>
   SCHOOL-SUPER: KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ The court-appointed
Desegregation Monitoring Committee will likely recommend it be
allowed to appoint a superintendent if the school board is unable
to reach agreement with a candidate by a court-imposed deadline of
July 19. By PHILLIP O'CONNOR. Story will move in the ``a''
