<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SOC-CUP-DEFENSE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LILLY USES HER HEAD IN VICTORY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRANK C. GIRARDOT  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA _ For Kristine Lilly, it was ``just a header.''
</P>
<P>
   As simple as that.
</P>
<P>
   For her American teammates, Lilly's dramatic goal-line save of a
Fan Yunjie header in the 100th minute of the Women's World Cup
final may have been the game's deciding moment.
</P>
<P>
   ``I saw the service and I watched the ball and thought I'd get a
head on it,'' Lilly said. ``It just bounced off my head and that
was that.''
</P>
<P>
   To some of her teammates, Lilly was doing a job.
</P>
<P>
   ``Kristine filled her role on that play,'' defender Brandi
Chastain said. ``She was where she had to be and made the play she
had to make.''
</P>
<P>
   But, to U.S. goalkeeper Brianna Scurry, Lilly's effortless play
was extraordinary.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had a little miracle today,'' Scurry said. ``I was like,
`Uh-oh. The ball is behind me.' I didn't know Lilly was behind me,
but I'm glad she was.''
</P>
<P>
   If anything, the play highlighted the tenacity of Team USA's
defense in a hard-fought game that ended in a 0-0 tie with China
before 90,185 who braved sweltering temperatures and high humidity.
</P>
<P>
   The game was ultimately decided on penalty kicks 5-4. The
outcome saved the reputation of a backfield that had been much
maligned leading up to the final match.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think that's the best defensive effort we've had this
tournament,'' defender Kate Sobrero said. ``I think we played great
defensively, we gave great coverage, we had some great individual
performances.''
</P>
<P>
   The team's strategy was to get the ball to Mia Hamm and Tiffeny
Milbrett on offense and let them create opportunities.
</P>
<P>
   ``We wanted to attack,'' head coach Tony DiCicco said. ``To
their credit, they are a very good defensive, too.''
</P>
<P>
   As the game wore on and the heat began to take its toll, the
defense realized it was time to take control, Sobrero said.
</P>
<P>
   ``We didn't talk about it, we just knew,'' she said. ``There was
no way that some country was going to come in here and take the
World Cup away from us in our own country. That's all we thought
about.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're in America, and if a breakdown happens (the defense was)
going to get killed for it. Winning was all we cared about.''
</P>
<P>
   DiCicco said he was proud of how the team pulled together.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought our defensive tactics and that part of our game plan
worked very well today,'' he said. ``But, I wish there had been
some goals so the crowd could enjoy the great attacking players on
the field.''
</P>
<P>
   As for Lilly's effort: ``Well, Kristine is one of the best
players in the world. She scores goals and denies top players. . .
. Full credit to Kristine Lilly.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
